Here's how to implement this in .NET MAUI Shell:

**1. Custom "Cancel" back button & navigation interception:**

```csharp
public partial class EditProductPage : ContentPage
{
    private bool _hasUnsavedChanges;

    public EditProductPage()
    {
        InitializeComponent();
        Shell.SetBackButtonBehavior(this, new BackButtonBehavior
        {
            Text = "Cancel",
            Command = new Command(async () => await TryNavigateBack())
        });
    }

    // Intercept hardware/gesture back button
    protected override bool OnBackButtonPressed()
    {
        if (_hasUnsavedChanges)
        {
            MainThread.BeginInvokeOnMainThread(async () => await TryNavigateBack());
            return true; // cancel default navigation
        }
        return false; // allow normal navigation
    }

    private async Task TryNavigateBack()
    {
        if (_hasUnsavedChanges)
        {
            bool leave = await DisplayAlert(
                "Unsaved Changes",
                "You have unsaved changes. Discard and leave?",
                "Discard", "Stay");

            if (!leave) return; // user chose to stay
        }

        await Shell.Current.GoToAsync("..");
    }
}
```

**Key points:**

- `Shell.SetBackButtonBehavior` replaces the back arrow with a "Cancel" button and routes taps through your command.
- `OnBackButtonPressed()` handles Android hardware back and swipe-back gestures. Return `true` to cancel navigation.
- On iOS, the swipe-back gesture isn't fully intercepted by `OnBackButtonPressed`. Setting `BackButtonBehavior` disables the default back button (and its gesture), so your command handles it.

Set `_hasUnsavedChanges = true` whenever a form field changes (e.g., via property change tracking or `Entry.TextChanged`).
